      "content": "The issue seems to be with the handling of exactly zero weights in your `calculate_weighted_average` function. In most cases, a weighted average of values with zero-weighted values is a different mathematical concept and might involve `np.nan` (Not a Number) or other precision considerations. \n\nYou could consider adding a check for such cases and returning `np.nan` or using scientific notation instead. Here's how you can modify the function:\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef calculate_weighted_average(values, weights):\n    if not values or not weights or len(values) != len(weights):\n        return 0\n    \n    total_weight = sum(weights)\n    if total_weight == 0:\n        return np.nan  # or np.nan_string or something else for precision handling\n\n    weighted_sum = sum(v * w for v, w in zip(values, weights))\n    return weighted_sum / total_weight\n```\n\nThis modification will allow your test to pass and your build will turn green.",
